The paper deals with handwritten character recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework employs a sequence to sequence model, which is a popular paradigm in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine translation (cs.IR). The use of deep learning techniques such as LSTM networks and Convolutional LSTM networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
